title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that finds all the purchases in the household appliances file for purchases made in october 2025. It should only include purchases for organisation which have more than 10 departments, also return the creditor name of these purchases as well as the price and the purchase line. Output in a textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log:
Build an Apache Wayang plan with the following specifications:

- Input:
  - Source: the “household appliances” file.
- Filtering criteria:
  - Purchase date is within October 2025.
  - Organisation has more than 10 departments (use the department count available in the data).
- Output fields:
  - Creditor name
  - Price
  - Purchase line
- Output:
  - Write the results to a text file.

log.thoughts: We need factpurchases for purchase lines and dates, creditor to get creditor name, department to compute organisations with >10 departments via organisation_id counts, and household_appliances as the keyword list for filtering invoice_line_descr.

steps.detailed_description: Load all required inputs: (a) text file household_appliances as lines (each line is one appliance term), (b) table factpurchases with all listed columns, (c) table department with all listed columns, and (d) table creditor with all listed columns.

Prepare datasets. For household_appliances: trim and lowercase each line to produce distinct appliance terms. For department: group by organisation_id and compute count(department_id); keep only organisation_id with department count > 10. For factpurchases: filter rows where invoice_date is between 2025-10-01 and 2025-10-31 (inclusive) and add a lowercase version of invoice_line_descr for later matching. Input: raw lines and tables from step 1. Output: (i) appliance_terms, (ii) orgs_over10 (organisation_id only), (iii) purchases_oct2025 (filtered factpurchases with helper lowercase description).

Semi-join purchases_oct2025 with orgs_over10 on organisation_id to keep only purchases from organisations having more than 10 departments. Input: purchases_oct2025 and orgs_over10. Output: purchases_large_orgs.

Filter purchase lines to only those related to household appliances by matching invoice_line_descr (lowercased) against appliance_terms. Implement as a containment/broadcast-style join: keep a purchase row if its lowercase invoice_line_descr contains any appliance term. Input: purchases_large_orgs and appliance_terms. Output: purchases_appliances_only.

Join purchases_appliances_only with creditor on creditor_id to fetch the creditor name. Join key: factpurchases.creditor_id = creditor.creditor_id. Input: purchases_appliances_only and creditor table. Output: purchases_with_creditor (includes creditor.name alongside purchase fields).

Project and format the final fields required by the user: Creditor name = creditor.name, Price = factpurchases.invoice_line_price, Purchase line = factpurchases.invoice_line_descr. Input: purchases_with_creditor. Output: final_result with exactly these three columns.
Write final_result to a text file as the output. Ensure each record contains the three fields in the desired order: Creditor name, Price, Purchase line.

log.thoughts: The plan loads the appliances file and relevant tables, prepares filters (date and org-size), applies an appliance-term match, enriches with creditor name, then projects and writes the requested fields. Steps are minimized while separating necessary joins and the final projection/output.
